Exception Handling – QUESTIONS ONLY (No Class)
Q1. Number Conversion
Write a program to:
•	Take a number as input
•	Convert it to integer
•	Handle invalid input
•	Print double of the number if valid
•	Always print "Conversion Done"

Q2. Average Calculator
Write a program to:
•	Take three numbers from user
•	Handle invalid input
•	Print average if no error occurs
•	Always print "Calculation Completed"

Q3. Password Length Check
Write a program to:
•	Take password input
•	Raise an exception if password length is less than 6
•	Handle invalid input
•	Print "Password Accepted" if valid
•	Always print "Password Check Finished"

Q4. Dictionary Value Access
Write a program to:
•	Create a dictionary {1: "Python", 2: "Java", 3: "C"}
•	Take key input from user
•	Handle key not found error
•	Print value if key exists
•	Always print "Dictionary Access Completed"

Q5. Sum of List Elements
Write a program to:
•	Create a list [10, 20, 30, 40]
•	Take index from user
•	Handle invalid input
•	Handle index out of range
•	Print element at index
•	Always print "List Operation Finished"

Q6. Simple Interest Calculator
Write a program to:
•	Take principal, rate, and time as input
•	Handle invalid input
•	Raise exception if any value is negative
•	Print simple interest if valid
•	Always print "Interest Calculation Done"

Q7. Username Validation
Write a program to:
•	Take username input
•	Raise exception if username contains digits
•	Handle invalid input
•	Print "Username Accepted" if valid
•	Always print "Validation Completed"

Q8. Email Validation
Write a program to:
•	Take email input
•	Raise exception if email does not contain @
•	Print "Valid Email" if correct
•	Handle exception properly
•	Always print "Email Check Finished"

Q9. Multiplication Table
Write a program to:
•	Take a number from user
•	Handle invalid input
•	Print multiplication table if valid
•	Always print "Table Generation Completed"

Q10. Safe Tuple Access
Write a program to:
•	Create tuple (5, 10, 15)
•	Take index from user
•	Handle invalid input
•	Handle index out of range
•	Print element if valid
•	Always print "Tuple Access Finished"

Q11. Calculator with Operator Check
Write a program to:
•	Take two numbers and an operator
•	Handle invalid input
•	Raise exception for invalid operator
•	Print result if valid
•	Always print "Calculator Finished"

Q12. File Write Operation
Write a program to:
•	Take file name from user
•	Write text into file
•	Handle permission error
•	Always print "File Write Completed"

Q13. Voting System
Write a program to:
•	Take age input
•	Raise exception if age is less than 18
•	Handle invalid input
•	Print "Allowed to vote" if valid
•	Always print "Voting Check Finished"
Q14. Temperature Conversion
Write a program to:
•	Take temperature in Celsius
•	Handle invalid input
•	Print temperature in Fahrenheit if valid
•	Always print "Conversion Finished"

Q15. Dictionary Update
Write a program to:
•	Create dictionary { "a": 1, "b": 2 }
•	Take key and value from user
•	Handle invalid input
•	Update dictionary
•	Always print "Update Completed"
